HEADWORD: Relucent
<hw>Re*lu"cent</hw> <pr>(r?-l?"s<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>relucens</ets>, p. pr. <ets>relucere</ets>. See
<er>Lucent</er>.]</ety> <def>Reflecting light; shining; glittering;
glistening; bright; luminous; splendid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gorgeous banners to the sun expand⟦br⟧
Their streaming volumes of <qex>relucent</qex> gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Glover.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reluct</ent>⟦br⟧
